Description: Two papyrus fragments; on one, 5 lines of Coptic text are written on one side along the fibres. On the other, which is very small, parts of one or two letters are preserved, written along the fibres. EA 75314, 75313, 75312, 75311, 75310, 75309 are mounted together.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380767) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380767)
